exercises.name: Dumbbell Chest Press
exercises.description: A chest press variation using dumbbells. This exercise is good to keep an even load on both sides of the chest.
exercises.benefits: Better range of motion allowing the lifter to activate the inner chest muscles a bit. Might also allow to lift in a better position.

exercises.name: Cable Crossover High to Low
exercises.description: Isolation exercise for the chest and front delts
exercises.benefits: the resistance curve with cables compared to dumbbells is more evenly distributed. The load on your chest muscles is therefore more constant

exercises.name: Incline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Performing the chest press with an incline increases the activation of your upper chest muscles
exercises.benefits: Using a barbell to perform the chest press allows for more load

exercises.name: Seated Dumbbell Overhead Press
exercises.description: Strong upper-body exercise for building your shoulders
exercises.benefits: Because you are sitting down you are reducing the need for core stabilization, which can increase form
